# SJMS 2.5 Conventions

## Stack facts
- Monorepo: `client/` (Next.js) + `server/` (Node/TS) npm workspaces
- DB: PostgreSQL via Prisma ORM (`prisma/schema.prisma`)
- Infra: Docker Compose (`docker-compose.yml`)
- Integrations: n8n, Moodle, Azure AD, SharePoint, Dynamics 365

## Build & test commands
- Install: `npm ci`
- Lint: `npm run lint`
- Build: `npm run build`
- Server dev: `npm run dev:server`
- Client dev: `npm run dev:client`
- Prisma generate: `npm run prisma:generate`
- Prisma migrate (dev only): `npm run prisma:migrate`

## Hard rules
1. Never log PII. Student names, DOB, email, address, and direct identifiers
   are PII under UK GDPR. Log internal IDs only.
2. Wrap multi-table writes in `prisma.$transaction`.
3. Validate all API inputs with Zod.
4. Use HESA field names for student attributes.
5. Do not modify auth, session, RBAC, or Prisma migrations without flagging
   `requires-human-review` and asking for explicit approval.
6. Do not disable tests or suppress type errors to make CI pass.

## Code style
- TypeScript `strict: true`
- Prefer named exports over default exports for shared modules
- Service layer in `server/src/services/*`; DB access in repositories, not routes
- Tests colocated in `__tests__/` adjacent to source

## Read-only Q&A mode
Comments starting with `@cursor explain`, `@cursor question:`, `@cursor q:`,
`@cursor what/why/how/where/when/which/who`, `@cursor describe`,
`@cursor summarise`, `@cursor summarize`, `@cursor review (no fix)`, or
`@cursor read-only:` are answered with a single comment only. No branches,
commits, or PRs are created. See `.cursor/agents/SJMS-Agent.md` for full rules.

## PR hygiene
- Commit prefix for agent-pushed fixes: `fix(agent):`
- Commit prefix for agent-implemented features: `feat(agent):`
- PR body must end with the self-review checklist from
  `.cursor/agents/SJMS-Agent.md`
